<subSubSection id="DDD273C36CB7FCB3AF8106878FE35685" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="comparisons">
<paragraph id="7EF47243DE11ECC94A458967251663BE" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Comparison.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C9B96BA87059F621C7F8D3E98EA762A1" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName id="0D6EF2AADCAEFF8522B352B3E30C9952" authorityName="Khalaim" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Probles" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Probles arkadyi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arkadyi">
<emphasis id="21609226EA7A340A159D50A175DF1739" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Probles arkadyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is easily distinguished from other Eastern Palaearctic species of the genus by its unusually small clypeus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="01F1E9AE2319F2B56CF0C4AA1B162CE2" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 1 habitus, lateral view 2 antennae, dorso-lateral view 3 head, front view 4 head, ventral view 5 head and mesoscutum, dorsal view 6 head and mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579261" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">3</figureCitation>
) which is 0.6 times as broad as the face (shortest distance between eye margins). A similarly small clypeus is known in the Vietnamese species 
<taxonomicName id="677572A0C89A92F3B3307B1F19088449" genus="P." lsidName="P. proshchalykini" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="proshchalykini">
<emphasis id="F2CB81AC16136522B17A5B83C760AD71" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">P. proshchalykini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Khalaim, 2019, but the latter species has genae strongly swollen behind the eyes (in dorsal view), while in 
<taxonomicName id="6AC3E5B0996230CF07E0A1138677EFFE" genus="P." lsidName="P. arkadyi" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="arkadyi">
<emphasis id="E8CCBF0DB6A02468B07872AF54507A1C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">P. arkadyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. the genae are distinctly constricted behind the eyes (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="11C8DC535548DFE16B6CA45F702B343F" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 1 habitus, lateral view 2 antennae, dorso-lateral view 3 head, front view 4 head, ventral view 5 head and mesoscutum, dorsal view 6 head and mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579261" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">5</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="BA16F2358FF1627C70E2DAB4B4428298" authorityName="Khalaim" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Probles" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Probles arkadyi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arkadyi">
<emphasis id="36FB3C7230D01104C4FD37D4FE4F3B17" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Probles arkadyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is also characterized by the long malar space and strongly tapered mandibles (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3036C001DB7A083168747145351D23CF" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 1 habitus, lateral view 2 antennae, dorso-lateral view 3 head, front view 4 head, ventral view 5 head and mesoscutum, dorsal view 6 head and mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579261" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DB1E3E492EFB31A315432CB6CA57EA98" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="description">
<paragraph id="F786ABD4977AFE9355A80F9DE7FBCFD2" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FDCA564366951B0EF3BD0C04579ED8D2" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="36086435207CEC0C417B80332600A5C9" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Female.</emphasis>
Body length 3.2 mm. Fore wing length 2.2 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8AD541544899E417AD31D26EA4F35CF4" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Head with gena distinctly and roundly constricted posterior to eyes (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4CEB7C3A1F5023D9F2D2063C2AB47354" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 1 habitus, lateral view 2 antennae, dorso-lateral view 3 head, front view 4 head, ventral view 5 head and mesoscutum, dorsal view 6 head and mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579261" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">5</figureCitation>
); gena in dorsal view 0.45 times as long as eye width. Clypeus unusually small, 2.1 times as broad as long and 0.6 times as broad as face (shortest distance between eye margins), smooth, with very fine and sparse punctures in upper half, separated from face by sharp furrow (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="07DF4FA1325A6A52CFB869D4BEDD90BE" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 1 habitus, lateral view 2 antennae, dorso-lateral view 3 head, front view 4 head, ventral view 5 head and mesoscutum, dorsal view 6 head and mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579261" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">3</figureCitation>
). Mandible strongly constricted in basal 0.7; width of mandible at level of teeth about 0.4 times width at base; lower tooth almost 1.5 times longer than the upper (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CD070C9788864EAD77AFFA6F0055E770" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 1 habitus, lateral view 2 antennae, dorso-lateral view 3 head, front view 4 head, ventral view 5 head and mesoscutum, dorsal view 6 head and mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579261" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">4</figureCitation>
). Malar space about 1.1 times as long as basal mandibular width. Flagellum with 16-17 flagellomeres, filiform (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="070EDFA1C0ED3C054B6366ADD2FB797C" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 1 habitus, lateral view 2 antennae, dorso-lateral view 3 head, front view 4 head, ventral view 5 head and mesoscutum, dorsal view 6 head and mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579261" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">2</figureCitation>
); second flagellomere almost twice, flagellomeres 3-5 about 1.8 times, and subapical flagellomeres 1.2 times as long as broad; flagellomeres 4 to 6 (or more) bearing very small subapical finger-shaped structures on outer surface (these structures hardly discernible with a light microscope). Face with median swelling. Face, frons and vertex finely granulate, impunctate, dull. Gena shallowly granulate, impunctate, weakly shining. Occipital carina complete, evenly convex mediodorsally. Hypostomal carina absent (at least in lower part).
</paragraph>
<caption id="B086E4B50B0FB7ED4599F685FE22E05A" doi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579261" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" start="Figures 1–6" startId="F1">
<paragraph id="FDF8F709B4DDAD8D7992A63FCED8F0C6" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="8D3C3255B1E402C8A72BABDF32618055" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Figures 1-6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="927047C83FCFF21B305EB40A5E2E9184" authorityName="Khalaim" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Probles" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Probles arkadyi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arkadyi">
<emphasis id="E27A82C265C2F3B2D85EAFC61C6D37AB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Probles arkadyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., holotype, female 
<emphasis id="6D5ECCC226D130FB0CD013DCB54CD046" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">1</emphasis>
habitus, lateral view 
<emphasis id="84A0D67123DDDFD22BB092909FC5B887" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">2</emphasis>
antennae, dorso-lateral view 
<emphasis id="31A8C5CD51E17B294C374B6CB468DB90" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">3</emphasis>
head, front view 
<emphasis id="C4925177C10D85E3647FFBB69C2C6140" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">4</emphasis>
head, ventral view 
<emphasis id="0350CC583B0FE1DBA0E69E392D882002" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">5</emphasis>
head and mesoscutum, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="CC5E0FDB0554A7A44EA3E0E6DB193744" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">6</emphasis>
head and mesosoma, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="D3FFEA8EA87B9C1C4C67FDC5CC83D578" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Mesosoma almost entirely granulate, impunctate and dull, except for mesopleuron, which is widely smooth and shining centrally above foveate groove (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="755D4CE739D5E1B913F3D9EBE0F265AC" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 1 habitus, lateral view 2 antennae, dorso-lateral view 3 head, front view 4 head, ventral view 5 head and mesoscutum, dorsal view 6 head and mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579261" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">6</figureCitation>
). Notaulus with irregular wrinkles (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BDF2321AB2F681E730AA15999DE70321" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 1 habitus, lateral view 2 antennae, dorso-lateral view 3 head, front view 4 head, ventral view 5 head and mesoscutum, dorsal view 6 head and mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579261" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">5</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with lateral longitudinal carinae developed on anterior 0.3-0.4. Upper end of epicnemial carina curved abruptly forward to anterior margin of mesopleuron (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6F014F319AA0F0E9A08A48D2F843BB93" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 1 habitus, lateral view 2 antennae, dorso-lateral view 3 head, front view 4 head, ventral view 5 head and mesoscutum, dorsal view 6 head and mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579261" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">4</figureCitation>
). Foveate groove of mesopleuron long, oblique, almost straight, deep and moderately broad, with distinct transverse wrinkles, extending over anterior 0.6 of mesopleuron, almost reaching epicnemial carina anteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AE12E6DEA190BD102E16FFEDF8AEDAF5" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 1 habitus, lateral view 2 antennae, dorso-lateral view 3 head, front view 4 head, ventral view 5 head and mesoscutum, dorsal view 6 head and mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579261" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">6</figureCitation>
). Propodeum with narrow to moderately broad basal area which is 2.5-3.5 times as long as broad and about half as long as apical area (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="82A4BCB1DCFC30374B1A2C0F77CF35E4" captionStart="Figures 7–11" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 11. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 7 wings 8 propodeum, dorsal view 9 base of metasoma, dorsal view 10 first tergite, lateral view 11 apex of metasoma with ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures7-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579262" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8</figureCitation>
). Propodeal spiracle separated from pleural carina by about 2.0 diameters of spiracle. Apical area slightly impressed along midline, narrowly rounded anteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0CA706ADF7CDC8D6555CA38491F52A19" captionStart="Figures 7–11" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 11. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 7 wings 8 propodeum, dorsal view 9 base of metasoma, dorsal view 10 first tergite, lateral view 11 apex of metasoma with ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures7-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579262" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8</figureCitation>
); apical longitudinal carinae complete and reaching transverse carina anteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="945A68620AD616227790FE5FFD20D68B" captionStart="Figures 7–11" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 11. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 7 wings 8 propodeum, dorsal view 9 base of metasoma, dorsal view 10 first tergite, lateral view 11 apex of metasoma with ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures7-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579262" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="319C770CCB9CB10D8A3093DD1F9CDF20" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Fore wing (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CDE402606870C20B71119D76A082EA08" captionStart="Figures 7–11" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 11. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 7 wings 8 propodeum, dorsal view 9 base of metasoma, dorsal view 10 first tergite, lateral view 11 apex of metasoma with ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures7-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579262" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">7</figureCitation>
) with second recurrent vein (2m-cu) postfurcal. First abscissa of radius (Rs+2r) straight, somewhat longer than width of pterostigma. First and second sections of radius (Rs+2r and Rs) meeting at slightly acute angle. Intercubitus (2rs-m) slightly thickened, about as long as abscissa of cubitus between intercubitus and second recurrent vein (abscissa of M between 2rs-m and 2m-cu). Metacarpus (R1) short, not reaching tip of the wing. Second abscissa of postnervulus (Cu&amp;2cu-a) present, thus brachial cell is closed posteriorly. Hind wing with nervellus (cu1&amp;cu-a) weakly reclivous. Legs slender, tarsal claws not pectinate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B15461F7B7F5C1FF73CA8C992EE4E732" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
First tergite about 3.4 times as long as posteriorly broad, more or less trapeziform in central cross-section; lateral sides of petiole distinctly longitudinally striate before glymma (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A0AE5392593EEABAF84B706E677A1C6A" captionStart="Figures 7–11" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 11. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 7 wings 8 propodeum, dorsal view 9 base of metasoma, dorsal view 10 first tergite, lateral view 11 apex of metasoma with ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures7-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579262" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">10</figureCitation>
), petiole dorsally and postpetiole smooth; glymma deep, round, situated at posterior 0.55 of tergite and joining by thin and sharp furrow with ventral part of postpetiole (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CF178AA3013619DBD83EE13013FDE318" captionStart="Figures 7–11" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 11. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 7 wings 8 propodeum, dorsal view 9 base of metasoma, dorsal view 10 first tergite, lateral view 11 apex of metasoma with ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures7-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579262" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">10</figureCitation>
); in dorsal view, petiole with lateral margins subparallel, postpetiole distinctly widened anteriorly and almost twice broader than petiole (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8BEAEDCF78F6BF0C431146F57AABFEAB" captionStart="Figures 7–11" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 11. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 7 wings 8 propodeum, dorsal view 9 base of metasoma, dorsal view 10 first tergite, lateral view 11 apex of metasoma with ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures7-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579262" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">9</figureCitation>
); upper margin of first tergite, in lateral view, nearly straight in anterior 0.7 and distinctly arcuate in posterior 0.3 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A214A352C02ECCDDBFAD79E41782752A" captionStart="Figures 7–11" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 11. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 7 wings 8 propodeum, dorsal view 9 base of metasoma, dorsal view 10 first tergite, lateral view 11 apex of metasoma with ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures7-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579262" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">10</figureCitation>
). Second tergite 1.5 times as long as anteriorly broad (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D3B3798E5DDB89C56A59AA49E433DD72" captionStart="Figures 7–11" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 11. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 7 wings 8 propodeum, dorsal view 9 base of metasoma, dorsal view 10 first tergite, lateral view 11 apex of metasoma with ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures7-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579262" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">9</figureCitation>
). Thyridial depression deep and long, 2.5-3.0 times as long as broad, with posterior end rounded (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B9F0ED1B28DE8D08FC4036F946F12923" captionStart="Figures 7–11" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 11. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 7 wings 8 propodeum, dorsal view 9 base of metasoma, dorsal view 10 first tergite, lateral view 11 apex of metasoma with ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures7-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579262" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">9</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor slender, weakly upcurved, with weak dorsal subapical depression (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="96510A19B934297F838498F0DB7A0A38" captionStart="Figures 7–11" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 11. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 7 wings 8 propodeum, dorsal view 9 base of metasoma, dorsal view 10 first tergite, lateral view 11 apex of metasoma with ovipositor, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures7-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579262" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">11</figureCitation>
); sheath twice as long as first tergite (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4FF5AAC041E90690F401D3318D1736D7" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 1 habitus, lateral view 2 antennae, dorso-lateral view 3 head, front view 4 head, ventral view 5 head and mesoscutum, dorsal view 6 head and mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579261" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="51C52F88A1C461E6C9839E8EF769A0CF" doi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures7-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579262" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" start="Figures 7–11" startId="F2">
<paragraph id="EC86213FCAFBADC8E1FDE636E372F7CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="01F84B8F5DBEAA583E29B6704053CB53" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Figures 7-11.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="52A77E18BFB81177BEB2D10489C64276" authorityName="Khalaim" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Probles" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Probles arkadyi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arkadyi">
<emphasis id="D2B19317068C9C61405FAA574D586FC8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Probles arkadyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., holotype, female 
<emphasis id="79696D3A0FBA873FEB5AB795AD4DF5E9" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">7</emphasis>
wings 
<emphasis id="43F4DF8A678C59777ECEFEA47E571108" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8</emphasis>
propodeum, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="DE1AB5E0A745C9F41DBF13CD59505D7D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">9</emphasis>
base of metasoma, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="E2BFD7E75AD61D006B1996BDCFCFF72B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">10</emphasis>
first tergite, lateral view 
<emphasis id="405E7C4624A7304929D3E6DB713B5C23" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">11</emphasis>
apex of metasoma with ovipositor, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="87A1817826D2072268110FB5160D50B4" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Head and mesosoma dark reddish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="27CCBD5396D250BDF7946EEB0E86CF38" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 1 habitus, lateral view 2 antennae, dorso-lateral view 3 head, front view 4 head, ventral view 5 head and mesoscutum, dorsal view 6 head and mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579261" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">6</figureCitation>
); lower 0.7 of clypeus, mouthparts and mandibles (teeth reddish black) yellow to brownish yellow. Antenna with scape and pedicel yellow ventrally and brownish dorsally; flagellum brown with basal flagellomeres yellowish brown. Tegula yellow-brown. Pterostigma brown. Legs brownish yellow; hind coxa slightly darkened with brown. First metasomal tergite dark brown. Metasoma posterior to first tergite predominantly brown, yellowish to pale brown ventrally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BA4684E96080CE72EE537E6F5C4B07BF" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Probles arkadyi sp. nov., holotype, female 1 habitus, lateral view 2 antennae, dorso-lateral view 3 head, front view 4 head, ventral view 5 head and mesoscutum, dorsal view 6 head and mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68719.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/579261" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ABAB72C6CC547E46AB59F61EE19015FD" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="26337DA7D455F447854B081A5BB9BE1A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1E4EC62F32195B6FD918D365129E334D" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C7CE1E3D37C02D15A8CA489360D9A554" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="870030E634E7CC315B81A4AC9CCB1442" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
The species is named in honour of the Russian entomologist, an expert in 
<taxonomicName id="A6795E307FDBD7EE78EC568A7542B42C" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Mutillidae</taxonomicName>
, Prof. Arkady S. Lelej (Vladivostok, Russia).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
